<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — three structured phases</h2>
  <p class="sub">Not a choice — every student does every phase. Total 75 min across solo prep, pair rehearsal, and AI rehearsal.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> {{ learningIntention | safe }}
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">1</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Solo prep (20 min)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Pick one question from each of the 6 categories. Sketch a 1-sentence answer for each. Notice which categories felt natural (probably Clarification + Evidence) and which felt hard (probably Devil's-advocate + Implementation). The hard ones are where today's work pays off. Pre-read the <a href="/foundations/defending-your-work/#strong-vs-weak">strong-vs-weak answer pair</a> before rehearsing — same skill, U0 topic; the categories rename but the moves don't.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">2</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Pair rehearsal (30 min)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">With a partner, swap defender / questioner roles. Partner picks 3 questions from the bank (their pick, not yours — that's the point). You answer each with timing: ≤30 seconds per response. Aim for <em>specific evidence</em> in each answer, not general "well, NASA says…". Switch roles. Both of you note where you stalled.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">3</div>
      <div class="choice-title">AI rehearsal (25 min)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Use the <a href="/ai-partners/defense-practice-partner/">Defense Practice Partner</a> for the categories your partner didn't cover — especially Devil's-advocate (peers can be reluctant to push hard, AI isn't). Ask for the toughest version of one question. Use the <a href="/ai-partners/the-skeptic/">Skeptic</a> if you want a sharper stress-test of your verdict itself. Document both exchanges.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="block-section show">
  <span class="section-tag">Show</span>
  <h2>What you're submitting today</h2>
  <p class="sub">Three components of the <a href="/units/unit-1/assessment-goldilocks-report/">Goldilocks Report</a> lock today — exoplanet analysis (T/T), cross-case synthesis (T/T), and AI Documentation log (K/U). Plus your Q&A rehearsal notes for tomorrow.</p>
  <div class="submission-callout">
    <div class="label">Component 4 — Exoplanet analysis (locks today)</div>
    <p>Your exoplanet's section of the Report — all 5–7 criteria evaluated, with MEETS / PARTIAL / FAILS / UNKNOWN verdicts and evidence cited. UNKNOWN is a legitimate verdict where the data don't exist. Trivial or partial analysis (1–2 criteria addressed) caps T/T-exoplanet at 3–4 Developing — see the <a href="/units/unit-1/assessment-goldilocks-report/">component watch-list</a>.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="submission-callout">
    <div class="label">Component 5 — Cross-case synthesis paragraph (locks today)</div>
    <p>One paragraph naming a <strong>non-obvious</strong> pattern across Earth + Mars + your exoplanet. Examples: "both Mars and Proxima b face atmospheric retention problems, but for different reasons" or "the habitable zone criterion is a necessary but very weak filter." Non-obvious is the T/T 7-8 move.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="submission-callout">
    <div class="label">Component 6 — AI Documentation log (locks today)</div>
    <p>Your complete AI Doc log to date — every substantive AI partner conversation that informed the Report, with OPVL on each AI response and the "one thing the AI got wrong" entry. If you used AI and this log isn't here, K/U-AI-Doc scores 1–2 Limited (the work isn't there to evaluate).</p>
    {% set submit = { id: "u1-b9", text: "Submit all three via Google Classroom" } %}{% include "partials/submit-link.njk" %}
  </div>
  <div class="submission-callout">
    <div class="label">Q&A rehearsal notes (formative — not strand-marked)</div>
    <p>Your 6 sketched answers from Solo prep (one per category) + identified strongest objection + planned response. One sentence per answer. Rehearsal data for tomorrow; not strand-marked.</p>
  </div>
